2000-06-12  Kaz Sasayama  <Kaz.Sasayama@hypercore.co.jp>

	* libvx68k/machine.cc (boot): Handle bus error and address error
	correctly.

	* bin/main.cc (run_boot): Catch special_exception.

	* libvx68k/doscontext.cc (start): Catch a special_exception.

	* libvm68k/execunit.cc (m68k_move_to_sr, m68k_move_from_usp,
	m68k_ori_to_sr, m68k_rte): Use privilege_violation_exception.

	* libvm68k/addrspace.cc (getw, getl, putw, putl): Throw
	address_error instead of bus_error.

	* libvm68k/memory.cc (bus_error): Removed.
	(generate_bus_error): Add argument bool read.  Use
	bus_error_exception.

	* include/vm68k/memory.h (class memory): Add an argument to member
	function generate_bus_error.  Also change all users.

	* include/vm68k/except.h (struct special_exception): New struct.
	(struct bus_error_exception): Renamed from bus_error.  Also change
	all users.
	(struct address_error_exception): Likewise.
	(struct bus_error_exception, struct address_error_exception): Use
	special_exception as a base.
	(struct ordinary_exception): New struct.
	(struct illegal_instruction_exception): Renamed from
	illegal_instruction.  Also change all users.
	(struct zero_divide_exception): Likewise.
	(struct privilege_violation_exception): Likewise.
	(struct illegal_instruction, struct zero_divide_exception, struct
	privilege_violation_exception): Use ordinary_exception as a base.

	* libvm68k/execunit.cc (m68k_bclr_r, m68k_bclr_i,
	m68k_move_from_sr): Add missing finish call.
	(m68k_move_from_sr): Fix diagnostic output.
	(m68k_move_to_sr): New function template.
	(initialize_instructions): Add new handlers.

	* libvx68k/systemrom.cc (getw): Generate a bus error for a program
	access.

	* bin/main.cc (parse_options): Handle `-b'.
	(display_help): Modify help messages.

	* libvx68k/systemrom.cc (initialize): Use 0xfe0000 as initial
	handler base address.
	(dispatch_iocs_function, iocs_trap): Likewise.

	* libvx68k/machine.cc (boot): Handle bus errors.

	* libvm68k/execunit.cc (m68k_add_m): Renamed from m68k_add_r.
	Also change all users.
	(m68k_sub_m): Renamed from m68k_sub_r.  Also change all users.
	(m68k_bclr_r): Modify diagnostic output.  Use variable value2.
	(m68k_bclr_i, m68k_move_from_sr): New function template.
	(bclrl_i): Disabled by #if-#endif.
	(m68k_ori_to_ccr): Use byte_type.  Modify diagnostic output.
	(m68k_ori_to_sr): New function.
	(initialize_instructions): Add new handlers.

	* libvx68k/systemrom.cc (iocs_b_readid): New function.
	(initialize_iocs_functions): Use the new function.

